translate:
Light on wealth, heavy on righteousness, heroic and wise;
The virtuous ruler and the talented minister are our guide.
Cao Cao's hunger led him to seek Zhong Yong's aid;
With a single word, he brought numerous ships back in row.

Standing in formation, a thousand bulls receive their orders;
With swords and scepters, they stand before the phoenix steps.
When a single command is given, the auspicious clouds gather;
The wild geese and herons follow, paying homage on both sides.

On the sea, a straw hat and fishing line hang for years;
In the vast wasteland, what can be known from its depths?
A straight hook catches no fish, nor do wives and children dwell in a snail's home;
Thirst quenched with cold spring water, hunger sated with purple mushrooms.
White hair covers both shoulders, a lofty spirit like a clear pond;
Once I heard an ancient sage speak, he was called the ancient owl.
Stone caves hide thunder and rain, golden pools nurture dragons and serpents;
Riding a wooden raft to the celestial river, riding a deer to wander the mountains of Emei;
Showing humanity either silent or speaking, dominating the world as a male or female;
Here lies the Baicui River, the leopard must change and wait for its time;
Since ancient times, the hidden and lost travelers are all teachers to kings.

Original marshland after frost, sweet grass turns yellow;
Barrier birds' messages carry a touch of resentment and beauty.
In autumn, the mountains are bathed in sunlight, revealing deer and antelope;
Southern flowers bloom amidst the snow and frost like a dream.
Smoke and fire illuminate nearby Pánhù customs;
Water and clouds drift deep into Wǔlíng villages.
Once I encountered Yiēkuī talking about the East Sea;
Always remembering Xīojiā's jade bed of indigo hue.

Smoke and rain hover in the south, a single leaf drifts by;
Pine-forested tarn, fishermen spend the night, relying on each other.
Fragments of sand, geese take flight, golden essence emerges;
Solitary peaks, monkeys mourn, woodland dwellers return.
Dreams of citrus fruits from the Chu Kingdom haunt me;
Red cliffs, cranes' voices echo, creating an ethereal harmony.
Unable to be like the old man of the vast ocean, I begin to miss my old nest;
I remember now, I'm tired of flying, ready to return home.

Looking at the sandbags again, the watchtower on the Long Pass is green with grass;
The new Lufan soldiers protect the Qiang troops in place of the departed.
Together they mourn the loss of their comrades, and in the night alone, the spirits cry out for their old encampment.

Recalling those days of leisure, when I wandered beyond worldly affairs;
The feathery beings once allowed to stay in the fairyland.
Basking in the warm smoke and mist by the creek, where we dried our herbs;
Spending endless hours playing chess beneath the flowers, as the sun and moon shone.
Stealing peaches from the tree, thinking of Manqing;
Transforming into a butterfly, learning from Meng Zhang.
Alas, the worldly ties still bind us, preventing us from returning to the tranquil forest and clear springs;
We can only longingly gaze at the woods and waters, longing to lose ourselves in their beauty.

Lying by the green creek, I contemplate ancient times;
Occasionally thinking of past events in the fading light.
The story of the painted butterfly remains, but its master is gone;
The dragon-carved pillar stands, yet its keeper is no longer there.
The sacred well's water has dried up, and the moss covers it;
The sacrificial altar's pine trees are bent, and the cranes have become rare.
In retrospect, I sigh for the fleeting nature of life;
In dreams, time seems to fly by as quickly as it can.

Eventful simplicity, opening a cup, with an easy mood;
Together enjoying the moonlight in the official residence.
Always ashamed that flowers lack the scenery of the River Yang;
Long embarrassed that there is no Single Father sound from the zither.
Unable to perform my duties as a government official;
Even if I act modestly, it's just a false reputation.
With you, we will strive to practice justice;
Dare to wait for the bright future in the prosperous era.
